---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import EditorialNote from "../components/EditorialNote.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Editorial Policy - WattCostGuide"
  description="How WattCostGuide researches, calculates, sources, reviews, and updates appliance electricity cost content."
>
  <section class="page-header">
    <p class="eyebrow">Editorial standards</p>
    <h1>Editorial Policy</h1>
    <p>How WattCostGuide builds practical estimates while keeping formulas, assumptions, and sources visible.</p>
  </section>

  <EditorialNote
    updated="June 21, 2026"
    note="This policy applies to WattCostGuide calculators, guides, category pages, and supporting methodology content."
  />

  <section class="section article-block">
    <h2>Purpose and scope</h2>
    <p>
      WattCostGuide publishes educational calculators and guides that help readers estimate appliance electricity
      use and running cost. Results are planning estimates, not utility billing, engineering, financial, or product
      purchase advice.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section article-block">
    <h2>Calculation standards</h2>
    <p>
      Cost estimates use the same visible formula across the site. Watts are converted to kilowatts, multiplied by
      runtime, and then multiplied by the electricity rate entered by the reader.
    </p>
    <pre><code>Cost = Watts / 1000 x Hours Used x Electricity Rate</code></pre>
    <p>
      Default wattage, runtime, and rate values are starting points. Readers are encouraged to replace them with
      an appliance nameplate, product manual, power-meter reading, and their own utility rate.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section article-block">
    <h2>Sources</h2>
    <p>
      We prefer first-party and authoritative sources such as the U.S. Energy Information Administration, U.S.
      Department of Energy, ENERGY STAR, utility documentation, appliance labels, owner manuals, and manufacturer
      specifications. Calculator pages identify the sources used for their method and operating context.
    </p>
    <p><a class="text-link" href="/references/">Review the site methodology and primary references</a>.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section article-block">
    <h2>Review and update dates</h2>
    <p>
      Calculator pages carry an independent last-reviewed date. A date changes when the page's assumptions,
      sources, calculation examples, or substantive explanations are reviewed. Minor formatting changes alone do
      not imply that every factual claim was newly reviewed.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section article-block">
    <h2>Advertising independence</h2>
    <p>
      Advertising does not determine calculator results, wattage assumptions, conclusions, or source selection.
      Sponsored placement, if introduced, will be labeled and kept separate from editorial calculations.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section article-block">
    <h2>Corrections and reader feedback</h2>
    <p>
      Readers can report unclear assumptions, broken sources, calculation issues, or appliance specifications.
      Substantive corrections are reviewed against reliable documentation and handled under the corrections policy.
    </p>
    <p><a class="text-link" href="/corrections/">Read the corrections policy</a>.</p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
